content: I was really looking forward to check the new CSX offer as a real alternative to challenger and neo banks such as revolut, neon and yapeal. Especially, since Credit Suisse does not have any cheap offer aside from the Bonviva packages which are bloated with options not everyone wants to use. I have to say I'm disappointed, the app is less appealing than revolut or neon counter-parts. The account opening process takes more than 10 minutes and has bugs (I never clicked on I have assets abroad which I want to take into Switzerland and still I was forced to answer from which country I want to move money to Switzerland?!?). Other apps offer photo ID verification and straight forward setup process, Credit Suisse does not. Also you need to make a video call and then wait a few days in which they send you 4 letters with activation code, credit card etc. I already have the SecureSign activated from a previous bank account but now it does not recognize it anymore. Every 2nd attempt works and login takes way too long (similar like how slow TWINT is). Also my older Credit Suisse accounts cannot be converted due to technical reasons... (I mean you pay Software Engineers to develop solutions right?). Additionally I get a new client relationship ID number to my old one which is already existing. Biggest drawback is again NO Google Pay integration as this card is not offered by Swisscard but SIX. If you have so much money and so much banking experience, how comes you are unable to offer a better package than fintech startups like neon, revolut or yapeal which have similar or better offers since a longer time? You really need to step up your game if you'd like to stay in business, get some good UX designers and get popular Apple Pay / Google Pay integration right from the start!
replyContent: Thank you very much for your feedback, which we will gladly forward internally. We are constantly developing and always strive to expand the app with additional helpful functions and make it even more attractive 😉 .
